alluxio.client.keyvalue

Class KeyValueWorkerClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • alluxio.AbstractClient
      • alluxio.client.keyvalue.KeyValueWorkerClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    alluxio.Client, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    @ThreadSafe
public final class KeyValueWorkerClient
extends alluxio.AbstractClient
    Client for talking to a key-value worker server. Since KeyValueWorkerClientService.Client is not thread safe, this class has to guarantee thread safety.

      • getNextKeys

        public List<ByteBuffer> getNextKeys(long blockId,
                                    ByteBuffer key,
                                    int numKeys)
                             throws IOException,
                                    alluxio.exception.AlluxioException
        Gets a batch of keys next to the current key in the partition.

        If current key is null, it means get the initial batch of keys. If there are no more next keys, an empty list is returned.

        Parameters:
        blockId - the id of the partition
        key - the current key
        numKeys - maximum number of next keys to fetch
        Returns:
        the next batch of keys
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs
        alluxio.exception.AlluxioException - if an Alluxio error occurs
